ce: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/aug/08/russia-ukraine-war-live-updates-moscow-missile-attack-pokrovsk-injuries-deaths" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/08/strictly-contestant-amanda-abbington-denies-being-transphobic" target="_blank">Strictly contestant Amanda Abbington denies being transphobic</a></h2><div class="description"> Sherlock actor apologises for ‘stupid’ and ‘ill-informed’ past comments after social media storm. Abbington, best known for TV shows including Sherlock and Mr Selfridge, was the first star to be announced for the BBC celebrity dancing show last week.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:54:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/08/strictly-contestant-amanda-abbington-denies-being-transphobic" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2023/aug/08/china-trade-exports-imports-slump-recovery-falters-ftse-stock-markets-inflation-business-live" target="_blank">Italy hits banks with windfall tax, sending shares sliding; China’s trade slumps – business live</a></h2><div class="description"> Italy approves 40% windfall tax on banks for 2023 as profits soar. Intesa and Sanpaolo's shares have tumbled almost 8%, while UniCredit’s are down over 6%. UK retailers forced to slash prices after July washout and interest rate rise.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:34:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/live/2023/aug/08/china-trade-exports-imports-slump-recovery-falters-ftse-stock-markets-inflation-business-live" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/painting-over-murals-for-children-at-asylum-centre-cost-home-office-1550" target="_blank">Painting over murals for children at asylum centre cost Home Office £1,550</a></h2><div class="description"> FoI request reveals cost of work at Manston centre in Kent, where cartoon murals meant to welcome children were painted over. Redecoration of walls at detention camp cost £1,549.52. Colourful characters whose images adorned the walls before the redecoration included Anna from the Disney movie Frozen and cartoon robins.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:00:26 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/painting-over-murals-for-children-at-asylum-centre-cost-home-office-1550" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/russian-strike-on-ukraine-city-kills-five-damaging-hotel-frequented-by-journalists" target="_blank">Russian strike on Ukraine city kills seven, damaging hotel used by journalists</a></h2><div class="description"> Two missile strikes on eastern Ukrainian city of Pokrovsk killed at least seven people and injured scores more. Hotel and pizzeria used by correspondents damaged in attack, say officials. Moscow said it had struck an ‘ordinary residential building’, publishing footage of a typical Soviet-era five-storey building.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 08:53:57 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/russian-strike-on-ukraine-city-kills-five-damaging-hotel-frequented-by-journalists" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/ruzzki-not-welcome-the-russian-exiles-getting-a-hostile-reception-in-georgia" target="_blank">‘Ruzzki not welcome’: the Russian exiles getting a hostile reception in Georgia</a></h2><div class="description"> Thousands of Russians fled to Tbilisi after the invasion of Ukraine. But the graffiti that has sprung up across the city suggests not everyone is pleased to see them. “I went from a place I didn’t feel at home to a place that is not welcoming me” says Dima Belysh.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/ruzzki-not-welcome-the-russian-exiles-getting-a-hostile-reception-in-georgia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/russia-releases-history-schoolbook-praising-ukraine-invasion" target="_blank">Russia releases history schoolbook praising Ukraine invasion</a></h2><div class="description"> Kremlin has tightened its control over the historical narrative in schools under Vladimir Putin. Trend has hugely accelerated since president launched full-scale war on Ukraine in 2022. Moscow has unveiled new history textbooks that defend Russia’s invasion of Ukraine before children return to school in September.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:35:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/russia-releases-history-schoolbook-praising-ukraine-invasion" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/ukraine-creates-database-of-art-linked-to-sanctions-hit-russians" target="_blank">Ukraine creates database of art linked to sanctions-hit Russians</a></h2><div class="description"> Ukraine’s National Agency on Corruption Prevention (NACP) has created a database of 300 pieces of art linked to sanctions. The database has been entered into a searchable database set up by the agency. It includes Leonardo da Vinci's Salvator Mundi and Andy Warhol's Four Marilyns.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/ukraine-creates-database-of-art-linked-to-sanctions-hit-russians" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/the-isometric-secret-15-ways-to-get-much-fitter-without-moving-a-muscle" target="_blank">The isometric secret: 15 ways to get much fitter – without moving a muscle</a></h2><div class="description"> The plank and wall sit are the best exercises to reduce your blood pressure. Here is how to do them – and some other great poses – whatever your current fitness level. Isometrics were most likely to reduce blood pressure, with full-body movements such as the wall squat showing bigger benefits than moves such  moves such as wall squat.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/the-isometric-secret-15-ways-to-get-much-fitter-without-moving-a-muscle" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/lauren-james-made-a-stupid-mistake-but-we-need-to-have-more-compassion-moving-the-goalposts-england-womens-world-cup" target="_blank">Lauren James made a stupid mistake – but we need to have more compassion | Suzy Wrack</a></h2><div class="description"> England forward lost composure against Nigeria but people need to take into account that players are human beings too. No one will be able to beat up James more than she will be doing to herself, so why pile on? Maybe this article shouldn’t exist either; perhaps picking over the bones of the incident feels unnecessary. Maybe there are broader points to be made about what level of criticism is appropriate in the women’s game, and the men's.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:50:17 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/lauren-james-made-a-stupid-mistake-but-we-need-to-have-more-compassion-moving-the-goalposts-england-womens-world-cup" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/william-friedkin-obituary" target="_blank">William Friedkin obituary</a></h2><div class="description"> American director behind two of the great film cult classics of the 1970s: The French Connection and The Exorcist. Friedkin had come to cinema through TV and documentary, but made a vital contribution to the American new wave. He was slightly older than the 'movie brats' group credited with revolutionising US cinema in the late 1960s and early 70s.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:31:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/william-friedkin-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/china-philippines-dispute-could-escalate-into-superpower-conflict-say-analysts" target="_blank">China-Philippines dispute could escalate into superpower conflict, say analysts</a></h2><div class="description"> Chinese coastguards used water cannon on a Philippine boat. Concerns growing as China expands and modernises its military. China shows increasing aggression in its claims over the South China Sea and Taiwan. Joint drills with Russia have also heightened concern over military coordination between Beijing and Moscow.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:23:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/china-philippines-dispute-could-escalate-into-superpower-conflict-say-analysts" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/guardian-readers-cinema-etiquette-bad-behavior-anecdotes" target="_blank">‘I always confront’: Guardian readers on the decline of cinema etiquette</a></h2><div class="description"> Reader walked out of a showing of Barbie at the Odeon last week due to the behaviour of other people in the cinema – they were scrolling through phones, chatting as if they were in their own front room, waving their arms in the air during the musical number and whooping every time Ryan Gosling's face appeared on screen.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 08:05:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/guardian-readers-cinema-etiquette-bad-behavior-anecdotes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/krystsina-tsimanouskaya-athletics-career-poland-belarus-interview" target="_blank">Krystsina Tsimanouskaya: ‘I’m sure my career would be over if I was in Belarus now’</a></h2><div class="description"> Krystsina Tsimanouskaya was ejected from Belarus team at the Tokyo Olympics. The sprinter has built a new life in Warsaw and won the right to run for Poland at this month’s world championships. She was ejected and fearing for her freedom if she returned home, sought refuge in Poland.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:20:19 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/krystsina-tsimanouskaya-athletics-career-poland-belarus-interview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/08/techscape-elon-musk-x-twitter-lawsuit-ccdh-hate-speech" target="_blank">TechScape: Why Elon Musk is taking trying to mute anti-hate-speech group</a></h2><div class="description"> Twitter alleges that the Center for Countering Digital Hate drove away advertisers – but CCDH and legal experts say otherwise. The social media company’s lawsuit against an anti-hate speech group is a key reason why Elon Musk bought Twitter for $44bn last year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:52:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/08/techscape-elon-musk-x-twitter-lawsuit-ccdh-hate-speech" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/08/nigel-slater-midweek-breakfast-grilled-greengages-bircher-muesli-and-maple-syrup" target="_blank">Nigel Slater’s recipe for grilled greengages, bircher muesli and maple syrup</a></h2><div class="description"> An unusual, luxurious take on a healthy fruity breakfast classic. Weigh 250g of greengages and cut each fruit in half. Sugar the fruit generously with 2 tbsp of caster sugar. Cook for 7-10 minutes until soft and lightly caramelised until soft.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:01:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/08/nigel-slater-midweek-breakfast-grilled-greengages-bircher-muesli-and-maple-syrup" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/sinead-o-connor-mental-illness-mainstream-debate" target="_blank">Forget Instagram hashtags, Sinéad O’Connor showed mental illness as it truly is | Hannah Jane Parkinson</a></h2><div class="description"> Sinéad O’Connor, who died last month at 56, went missing in March 2016. The Telegraph ran a live blog on the singer’s whereabouts after she had posted suicidal thoughts. I pointed out to an editor at the paper that rolling updates about a person going through a severe mental health episode, an episode that might have ended fatally, was a mistake.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:16:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/sinead-o-connor-mental-illness-mainstream-debate" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/its-almost-18-months-since-russia-invaded-ukraine-and-peace-seems-no-closer" target="_blank">It’s almost 18 months since Russia invaded Ukraine, and peace seems no closer | Rajan Menon</a></h2><div class="description"> Initiatives aimed at ending the war that Russia started by invading Ukraine have been underway for months. On 24 February – a year to the day Russia started its attack – China unveiled a proposal containing 12 principles. In June, a group of African leaders met separately with Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskiy and Russian president Vladimir Putin to present a peace plan.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:13:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/its-almost-18-months-since-russia-invaded-ukraine-and-peace-seems-no-closer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/refugee-barges-sewage-e-coli-why-would-anyone-like-to-be-beside-the-seaside" target="_blank">Refugee barges! Sewage! E coli! Why would anyone like to be beside the seaside? | Zoe Williams</a></h2><div class="description"> Dorset is mainly in the news because of the giant refugee barge that has just taken delivery of its first residents. Even if you couldn’t see it from your beach hut – it would be charming to go to a Dorset beach when the area is.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/refugee-barges-sewage-e-coli-why-would-anyone-like-to-be-beside-the-seaside" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/halt-taliban-repression-afghan-women-girls-education" target="_blank">The world must unite now to halt the Taliban’s repression of Afghan women and girls | Gordon Brown</a></h2><div class="description"> Two years of ever-intensifying repression have not dimmed the resilience of girls and women in Afghanistan. It is time to declare it a crime against humanity, and prosecutors of the international criminal court (ICC) should open an investigation into the repression. Afghanistan's permanent representative of Afghanistan to the U.N. has called it a 'gender apartheid'</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/halt-taliban-repression-afghan-women-girls-education" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/rishi-sunak-anti-green-extremists" target="_blank">Here’s what we know about Sunak now: where the anti-green extremists lead, he will follow | Polly Toynbee</a></h2><div class="description"> Prime Minister Rishi Sunak was apparently spotted in a gym at 7am in Santa Monica, California. His family owns a £5.5m penthouse in a building with its own pet spa. 57 world triathlon athletes in Sunderland have just fallen ill in a triathlon.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 07:00:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/rishi-sunak-anti-green-extremists" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/britain-poor-people-leisure-victorian-workhouse" target="_blank">Britons have become so mean that many of us think poor people don’t deserve leisure time | Frances Ryan</a></h2><div class="description"> 76% of Britons believe that everyone should be able to afford utility bills. 74% think they should have the means to eat a balanced diet. A quarter of the public believe that people on out-of-work benefits shouldn’t have electricity or vitamins. Only 60% think seasonal celebrations should be attainable for all.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 05:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/britain-poor-people-leisure-victorian-workhouse" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/hollywood-strike-sag-wga-studio-greed-disney-universal" target="_blank">The Hollywood strike drags on because of one stumbling block: studio greed | Kathleen Sharp</a></h2><div class="description"> The Screen Actors Guild is still on strike, studio tycoons sound like Logan Roy and the two-union shutdown could drag on for months. Writers and actors want raises, residuals from streaming platforms and some regulation of AI, says Kathleen Sharp. Sharp is the author of Mr &amp; Mrs Hollywood and co-producer of The Last Mogul.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:10:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/08/hollywood-strike-sag-wga-studio-greed-disney-universal" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/bbc-6-music-radio-station" target="_blank">From weird nostalgia to weak formats, 6 Music is having an identity crisis | Daniel Dylan Wray</a></h2><div class="description"> The 6 Music Dad character – referring to the BBC radio station – is part harmless joke, part slur. Broadly speaking, it’s aimed at people who had their formative musical years somewhere between the late 1970s and early 90s. 6 Music is a one-stop-shop for alternative music if you’ve no desire to search further afield.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:05:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/bbc-6-music-radio-station" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/the-guardian-view-on-the-bibby-stockholm-a-gesture-of-self-defeating-cruelty" target="_blank">The Guardian view on the Bibby Stockholm: a gesture of self-defeating cruelty | Editorial</a></h2><div class="description"> Home Office is doomed to failure for as long as it insists on treating refugees like criminals. Asylum is granted on the basis of need, not as a conditional judgment of the route taken. Asylum seekers should not be treated as effective prisoners while their claims are being processed, says Rishi Sunak.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 17:30:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/07/the-guardian-view-on-the-bibby-stockholm-a-gesture-of-self-defeating-cruelty" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/07/no-justice-in-our-battle-against-domestic-abuse" target="_blank">No justice in our battle against domestic abuse | Letters</a></h2><div class="description"> The hundreds of women who want to tell their story of domestic abuse should send their work to a collective, and the names of the authors should be revealed. To protect their children, the abuse can be perpetuated through them, says the author. She says no court has found the family abuser guilty of anything and he could sue her for defamation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 15:22:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/07/no-justice-in-our-battle-against-domestic-abuse" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/07/the-climate-cost-of-scouts-ill-judged-south-korea-jamboree" target="_blank">The climate cost of scouts’ ill-judged South Korea jamboree | Letter</a></h2><div class="description"> 4,500 scouts from the UK, each having flown for more than three weeks, have flown to South Korea for the jamboree. The Scouts’ website states: “We know how important tackling climate change is and that’s why we empower young people with the skills to campaign at a local, national and international level.”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 15:21:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/07/the-climate-cost-of-scouts-ill-judged-south-korea-jamboree" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/colombia-jamaica-womens-world-cup-last-16-match-report" target="_blank">Colombia’s Catalina Usme ends Jamaica hopes to set up England quarter-final</a></h2><div class="description"> Colombia will progress to the last eight for the first time thanks to a second-half goal from their captain, Catalina Usme. Neither team has ever made the quarter-finals before and both had helped send powerhouses home early from the group stage. Colombia's fairytale was cut short by Colombia's goal.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:19:09 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/colombia-jamaica-womens-world-cup-last-16-match-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/07/england-stagger-on-at-the-world-cup-but-towards-destiny-or-the-trapdoor" target="_blank">England stagger on at the World Cup – but towards destiny or the trapdoor? | Jonathan Liew</a></h2><div class="description"> Nobody expected it to get this far a few hours ago, but then nobody expected Germany to go out in the group stage a few days ago, and nobody expected women’s football to be played in front of sell-out crowds of 50,000 a few years ago. The history of women's football is not written on the balance of probabilities.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 14:51:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/07/england-stagger-on-at-the-world-cup-but-towards-destiny-or-the-trapdoor" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/08/caitlin-foord-matildas-player-australia-womens-world-cup-2023" target="_blank">Speed, skill and scoring: Caitlin Foord rises to Women’s World Cup challenge | Kieran Pender</a></h2><div class="description"> Caitlin Foord is at her blistering best on the counter-attack, when she launches herself like a rocket down the left flank. Foord has variety in her attacking arsenal, but she can outwit defenders as she runs at them with the ball; she can pass her way through most midfields.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 05:05:17 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2023/aug/08/caitlin-foord-matildas-player-australia-womens-world-cup-2023" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/premier-league-2023-24-preview-no-14-manchester-united" target="_blank">Premier League 2023-24 preview No 14: Manchester United</a></h2><div class="description"> Manchester United are expected to finish third in the Premier League this season. Erik ten Hag is helping the club back on its feet and arrival of Mason Mount and André Onana is reason for optimism. But the club’s ownership needs to be resolved, says The Guardian.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:00:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/premier-league-2023-24-preview-no-14-manchester-united" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/wolves-gary-oneil-manager-julen-lopetegui" target="_blank">Wolves line up Gary O’Neil as manager with Julen Lopetegui poised for exit</a></h2><div class="description"> Julen Lopetegui's future in extreme doubt with future in doubt. Gary O’Neil poised to take over days before the start of the season. Wolves are concerned his frustrations could damage dressing-room morale. O'Neil out of work after sacking by Bournemouth in June.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:36:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/wolves-gary-oneil-manager-julen-lopetegui" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/england-world-cup-squad-steve-borthwick-breakdown-rugby-union" target="_blank">The Breakdown | Borthwick’s World Cup squad short on fizz and leaning on England’s past</a></h2><div class="description"> England's 33-man Rugby World Cup party for France is certainly not one to encourage much champagne-fuelled excitement among connoisseurs of expansive, enterprising rugby. England appear primarily intent on hoofing it high, chasing hard, relying on their set piece and kicking their goals.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:22:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/england-world-cup-squad-steve-borthwick-breakdown-rugby-union" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/people-were-telling-us-to-go-home-relegation-and-revival-at-burnley" target="_blank">‘People were telling us to go home’: relegation and revival at Burnley</a></h2><div class="description"> Clarets’ chairman Alan Pace reveals the abuse he received as Vincent Kompany looks to keep building. Pace insists he was reluctant to let the cameras in, and uncomfortable in front of them, but he and his fellow board members feature heavily in a four-parter that covers the sacking of Sean Dyche, relegation from the Premier League, appointment and Burnley's Championship triumph.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/people-were-telling-us-to-go-home-relegation-and-revival-at-burnley" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/man-dies-after-violent-clashes-between-aek-athens-and-dinamo-zagreb-fans" target="_blank">Man dies after violent clashes between AEK Athens and Dinamo Zagreb fans</a></h2><div class="description"> 29-year-old stabbed in incident on Monday night in Athens. Tuesday’s Champions League qualifier has been postponed. Police said 100 to 120 Dinamo fans had shown up late on Monday near the AEK stadium, and where AEK fans had gathered. AEK Athens and Dinamo Zagreb fans gathered outside AEK's stadium in Nea Philadelphia.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:02:19 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/08/man-dies-after-violent-clashes-between-aek-athens-and-dinamo-zagreb-fans" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/federico-bahamontes-first-spanish-tour-de-france-winner-dies-aged-95" target="_blank">Federico Bahamontes, first Spanish Tour de France winner, dies aged 95</a></h2><div class="description"> The first Spaniard to win the Tour de France, Federico Bahamontes, has died at the age of 95, Spanish officials say. The Spaniard was the first cyclist to complete a “career triple” by winning the “King of the Mountains” classification in all three Grand Tours. He earned the nickname “The Eagle of Toledo” after numerous victories in mountain stages.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:13:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/federico-bahamontes-first-spanish-tour-de-france-winner-dies-aged-95" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/07/eilinor-barker-and-neah-evans-win-world-madison-gold-for-britain" target="_blank">Elinor Barker and Neah Evans win world championship Madison gold for Britain</a></h2><div class="description"> British pair hold off Australia after crash forces late restart. Barker and Evans had to fight hard in final nine laps to hold off closest challengers Australia by just three points. Barker already a gold medallist in the women’s team pursuit at the UCI world championships in Glasgow.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 20:14:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/07/eilinor-barker-and-neah-evans-win-world-madison-gold-for-britain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/anthony-joshua-to-face-robert-helenius-at-o2-arena-after-whyte-cancellation-boxing" target="_blank">Anthony Joshua to face Robert Helenius at O2 Arena after Whyte cancellation</a></h2><div class="description"> Anthony Joshua will fight Robert Helenius at London’s O₂ Arena on Saturday night. Finnish boxer was confirmed as Dillian Whyte's replacement after ‘adverse analytical findings’ were detected in a doping test conducted by Whyte. ‘I plan to make the most of it,’ says 39-year-old fighter.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:44:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/08/anthony-joshua-to-face-robert-helenius-at-o2-arena-after-whyte-cancellation-boxing" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/canadian-wildfire-fighters-scramble-amid-nightmare-season" target="_blank">How the climate crisis has changed wildfire fighting in Canada: ‘a chess game with Mother Nature’</a></h2><div class="description"> The Donnie Creek wildfire is the largest in British Columbia history. At more than 583,000 hectares (1.4m acres), it is larger than the Canadian province of Prince Edward Island. It could swallow nine areas the size of New York City without blinking.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:00:26 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/canadian-wildfire-fighters-scramble-amid-nightmare-season" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/07/in-the-absence-of-solutions-tackling-the-causes-of-antibiotic-resistance-is-key" target="_blank">In the absence of solutions, tackling the causes of antibiotic resistance is key</a></h2><div class="description"> The emergence of a possible link between air pollution and antibiotic resistance shows why action to clean up air is so badly needed. A decade ago, Britain’s top health official issued a grim warning: <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/2013/jan/23/antibiotic-resistant-diseases-apocalyptic-threat"</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 22:30:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/07/in-the-absence-of-solutions-tackling-the-causes-of-antibiotic-resistance-is-key" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/aug/08/climate-heating-gas-released-from-dozens-of-australian-fossil-fuel-sites-environmental-group-claims" target="_blank">Climate-heating methane released from dozens of Australian fossil fuel sites, environmental group claims</a></h2><div class="description"> Energy giants reject Australian Conservation Foundation’s infrared video investigation which claims gas leaks and venting at dozens of mines and facilities. Climate-heating methane gas is leaking or being vented from more than 100 places across 35 fossil fuel sites in Queensland and New South Wales.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/aug/08/climate-heating-gas-released-from-dozens-of-australian-fossil-fuel-sites-environmental-group-claims" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/drastic-action-needed-to-limit-worsening-extreme-events-in-antarctica-scientists-warn" target="_blank">‘Virtually certain’ extreme Antarctic events will get worse without drastic action, scientists warn</a></h2><div class="description"> Record low sea ice levels, the collapse of ice shelves, and surface temperatures 38.5C above average cited as concerns in new review. It is “virtually certain” that future extreme events in <a href="https://://://www.gutools.co.uk/world/antarctica">Antarctica will be worse than the extrao.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 04:31:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/drastic-action-needed-to-limit-worsening-extreme-events-in-antarctica-scientists-warn" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/07/air-pollution-linked-rise-antibiotic-resistance-imperils-human-health" target="_blank">Air pollution linked to rise in antibiotic resistance that imperils human health</a></h2><div class="description"> Air pollution is helping to drive a rise in antibiotic resistance that poses a significant threat to human health worldwide, a global study suggests. The analysis, using data from more than 100 countries spanning nearly two decades, indicates that increased air pollution is linked with rising antibiotic resistance across every country and continent.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 22:30:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/07/air-pollution-linked-rise-antibiotic-resistance-imperils-human-health" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/08/palantir-lobbied-uk-disabilities-minister-software-benefits-fraud" target="_blank">Palantir lobbied UK disabilities minister to use software to tackle benefits fraud</a></h2><div class="description"> US data firm wanted to brief Tom Pursglove on how its technology could help recover ‘large amounts’ of fraud. Palantir wrote to the UK disabilities minister to brief him on technology it had recently deployed elsewhere. The company promised that it had the potential for the Department for Work and Pensions to rapidly “recover large amounts of fraud”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 05:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/08/palantir-lobbied-uk-disabilities-minister-software-benefits-fraud" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/cornish-lithium-secures-536m-to-open-first-mine-for-the-metal-in-britain" target="_blank">Cornish Lithium secures £53.6m to open first mine for the metal in Britain</a></h2><div class="description"> UK Investment Bank leads funding of project to extract compounds used for electric vehicle batteries. ‘The part of Cornwall nobody ever sees’: the hi-tech future for lithium and tin mining.’s first lithium mine in Cornwall secured $67m (£53.6m) of investment led by the UK Infrastructure Bank.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:19:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/08/cornish-lithium-secures-536m-to-open-first-mine-for-the-metal-in-britain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/west-midlands-mayor-calls-for-crooked-house-pub-to-be-rebuilt-brick-by-brick" target="_blank">West Midlands mayor calls for Crooked House pub to be rebuilt ‘brick by brick’</a></h2><div class="description"> Andy Street has called for the Crooked House pub to be ‘rebuilt brick by brick’ after it was demolished following a huge fire over the weekend. The building, known as the Britain’s ‘wonkiest pub’ and dating back to 1765, was gutted by a fire on Saturday night.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 08:19:19 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/west-midlands-mayor-calls-for-crooked-house-pub-to-be-rebuilt-brick-by-brick" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/scottish-exams-pass-rate-falls-for-second-successive-year" target="_blank">Scottish exams pass rate falls for second successive year</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 144,000 school students received their National, Higher and Advanced Higher exam grades on Tuesday. Pass rates for Highers fell from 78.9% last year to 77.1% in Scotland. Grading system became stricter after the Covid pandemic, with pass rates falling for second successive year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:20:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/scottish-exams-pass-rate-falls-for-second-successive-year" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/08/britishvolt-buyer-yet-to-make-final-payment-in-deal-to-rescue-battery-firm" target="_blank">Britishvolt buyer yet to make final payment in deal to rescue battery firm</a></h2><div class="description"> Recharge Industries failed to make the final payment in its purchase of Britishvolt. The Australian firm bought the failed battery firm for £8.57m earlier this year. The deal was finalised in February but Recharge has yet to make final payment, due on 5 April. Britishvolt’s administrators, EY, said the buyer had yet to pay.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:08:59 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/08/britishvolt-buyer-yet-to-make-final-payment-in-deal-to-rescue-battery-firm" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/08/firm-behind-voice-of-gamblers-group-co-owned-by-betting-industry-consultant" target="_blank">Firm behind ‘voice of gamblers’ group co-owned by betting industry consultant</a></h2><div class="description"> Gamblers Consumer Forum aims to derail planned gambling reforms and claims to act on behalf of ordinary punters. The group is co-owned by a consultant for the betting industry. Ministers proposed a series of changes in April that they said would make gambling safer by imposing tighter regulations on online betting firms.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 05:00:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/08/firm-behind-voice-of-gamblers-group-co-owned-by-betting-industry-consultant" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/premium-bonds-prize-fund-rises-to-highest-level-in-24-years" target="_blank">Premium bonds prize fund rises to highest level in 24 years</a></h2><div class="description"> NS&amp;I, the government-backed organisation that runs the monthly draw, said it would increase the rate from 4% to 4.65% next month. The increase will add £66m to the prize fund, which is the highest level in 24 years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:58:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/premium-bonds-prize-fund-rises-to-highest-level-in-24-years" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/urban-foxes-no-more-cunning-than-rural-ones-researchers-find" target="_blank">Urban foxes no more cunning than rural ones, researchers find</a></h2><div class="description"> City dwellers just as likely to be too ‘shy or lazy’ to solve puzzle for food as their country cousins, study finds. Red foxes are among the most successful carnivores in the world. Number living in British towns and cities has exploded in recent years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 04:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/urban-foxes-no-more-cunning-than-rural-ones-researchers-find" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/08/small-firms-fear-going-bust-amazon-extends-wait-time-sale-proceeds" target="_blank">Small firms fear going bust as Amazon extends wait time for sale proceeds</a></h2><div class="description"> Amazon has told thousands of marketplace sellers in the UK and continental Europe it will hold on to sale proceeds for more than a week. Sellers in UK and rest of Europe say having to wait over a week means they will struggle to pay staff and loans. Amazon has written to sellers to inform them it will no longer credit their accounts as soon as a sale is made online.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 05:00:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/08/small-firms-fear-going-bust-amazon-extends-wait-time-sale-proceeds" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/us-and-eu-leaders-urged-to-change-tack-on-kosovo-serbia-tensions" target="_blank">US and EU leaders urged to change tack on Kosovo-Serbia tensions</a></h2><div class="description"> Politicians including chairs of US and UK foreign affairs committees criticise ‘lack of pressure placed on Serbia’ They have written to US and EU leaders to urge them to reconsider their approach to easing tensions between Kosovo and Serbia. They say the ‘EU-facilitated dialogue has yet to yield positive results’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:58:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/us-and-eu-leaders-urged-to-change-tack-on-kosovo-serbia-tensions" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/firefighters-tackling-blaze-raging-in-southern-portugal-fire" target="_blank">Hundreds of firefighters tackling blaze raging in southern Portugal</a></h2><div class="description"> Fire has scorched thousands of hectares of land and forced precautionary evacuation of 1,400 people. Started on Saturday in the municipality of Odemira in the Alentejo region but has since spread south towards the Algarve, one of Portugal’s top tourist destinations.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:45:19 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/firefighters-tackling-blaze-raging-in-southern-portugal-fire" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/08/sales-at-vegan-burger-maker-beyond-meat-fall-by-almost-a-third" target="_blank">Sales at vegan burger maker Beyond Meat fall by almost a third</a></h2><div class="description"> US firm cuts revenue forecast as consumers opt for cheaper animal protein amid cost of living crisis. Beyond Meat's plant-based products include burgers that appear to bleed and imitations of sausages and meatballs. US firm has cut its annual revenue forecast in latest sign that the vegan food bubble is bursting.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 07:33:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/08/sales-at-vegan-burger-maker-beyond-meat-fall-by-almost-a-third" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/08/menstrual-discs-may-be-better-for-heavy-periods-than-pads-or-tampons-study" target="_blank">Menstrual discs may be better for heavy periods than pads or tampons – study</a></h2><div class="description"> First study to compare absorption of period products using human blood finds that discs can hold the most. Discs may be better than traditional pads or tampons for dealing with heavy monthly blood flow. Findings could also help doctors better assess whether heavy menstrual bleeding could be a sign of underlying health problems.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 07:39:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/08/menstrual-discs-may-be-better-for-heavy-periods-than-pads-or-tampons-study" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/megan-thee-stallion-shooting-sentencing-tory-lanez" target="_blank">Sentencing in Megan Thee Stallion shooting stretches into second day</a></h2><div class="description"> The sentencing hearing for the musician Tory Lanez will stretch into a second day on Tuesday. Lanez was found guilty in December 2022 of shooting the fellow artist <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/megan-thee-stallion-shooting-sentencing-tory-lanez"</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:48:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/megan-thee-stallion-shooting-sentencing-tory-lanez" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/trump-evidence-witness-transcripts-january-6" target="_blank">Prosecutors seek to prevent Trump from sharing January 6 case evidence</a></h2><div class="description"> Federal prosecutors asked a federal judge to reject Donald Trump's request for fewer restrictions over how he can publicly share evidence in the case involving his efforts to subvert the 2020 election. Trump's lawyers want the ability to widely share some evidence, including sensitive witness transcripts. Prosecutors argue the former president was seeking to abuse the discovery process.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 01:59:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/07/trump-evidence-witness-transcripts-january-6" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/desantis-claims-agents-can-tell-traffickers-from-migrants-in-call-for-deadly-force" target="_blank">DeSantis claims agents can tell traffickers from migrants in call for deadly force</a></h2><div class="description"> Rightwing Florida governor and 2024 presidential hopeful Ron DeSantis has sparked controversy by outlining a hardline border policy of deadly force despite acknowledging that drug traffickers could be difficult to distinguish from migrants crossing into the US. Under his direction as president, US law enforcement on the lookout for drugs would not mistakenly use lethal force on migrants.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/desantis-claims-agents-can-tell-traffickers-from-migrants-in-call-for-deadly-force" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/new-orleans-archbishop-gregory-aymond-concealed-clerical-sex-abuse-claims" target="_blank">New Orleans archbishop ignored board findings on clerics accused of abuse</a></h2><div class="description"> Gregory Aymond promised ‘to be transparent’ – but a Guardian investigation found that he hid allegations. An expert questions whether it was against Vatican policy to hide allegations against priests and deacons. The board which helps the Roman Catholic archbishop of New Orleans evaluate abuse allegations in six cases found clergymen to be credibly accused.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:00:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/08/new-orleans-archbishop-gregory-aymond-concealed-clerical-sex-abuse-claims" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/dj-casper-who-had-no-1-hit-with-cha-cha-slide-dies-aged-58" target="_blank">DJ Casper, who had No 1 hit with Cha Cha Slide, dies aged 58</a></h2><div class="description"> DJ Casper created Cha Cha Slide in 1998 as a musical exercise routine for his personal trainer nephew. He had been diagnosed with kidney and liver cancer in 2016, and died from the illness. Casper was born Willie Perry Jr in Chicago where he continued to live, but died from illness.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 07:55:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/dj-casper-who-had-no-1-hit-with-cha-cha-slide-dies-aged-58" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/marvel-vfx-artists-take-first-step-toward-unionisation-amid-hollywood-strikes" target="_blank">Marvel VFX artists take first step toward unionisation amid Hollywood strikes</a></h2><div class="description"> A group of on-set VFX artists employed by the studio have filed a petition with the US’s National Labor Relations Board. The International Alliance of Theatrical Stage Employees (IATSE) said a supermajority of Marvel's 50-plus VFX crew had signed authorisation cards indicating they wished to be represented by the union.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:31:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/marvel-vfx-artists-take-first-step-toward-unionisation-amid-hollywood-strikes" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/08/strategic-love-play-review-witty-ins-and-outs-of-the-dating-game" target="_blank">Strategic Love Play review – witty ins and outs of the dating game</a></h2><div class="description"> Miriam Battye’s comedic tour de force, Her and Him go through the motions of getting to know each other. If they finish one pint, they will have fulfilled the obligation to be polite. Two and they might even like each other. Two and three.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:44:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/08/strategic-love-play-review-witty-ins-and-outs-of-the-dating-game" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/variety-review-fierce-feminist-porn-drama-from-the-80s-new-york-underground" target="_blank">Variety review – fierce feminist porn drama from the 80s New York underground</a></h2><div class="description"> Variety, directed by Bette Gordon, is re-released for its 40-year anniversary. It is a flawed but fascinating critique of the male gaze, the porn gaze and the luxurious ordeal of guilty voyeurism. Gordon casts a female lead, flipping gender assumptions and turning the tables on the underworld quest-torments of Paul Schrader’s male heroes in the likes of Taxi Driver and Hardcore.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 06:00:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/08/variety-review-fierce-feminist-porn-drama-from-the-80s-new-york-underground" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/08/the-well-of-saint-nobody-by-neil-jordan-review-the-film-makers-new-novel-is-full-of-marvels" target="_blank">The Well of Saint Nobody by Neil Jordan review – the film-maker’s new novel is full of marvels</a></h2><div class="description"> The Well of Saint Nobody is Neil Jordan’s beautiful and deceptively simple tale of love, rejuvenation and losses restored. It is a reminder of Jordan's gifts as a writer, says the author. West Cork is a place apart, but something of the old magic survives. It pervades the story of a once successful concert pianist who finds love and rejuvenation before mystical forces intervene.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 06:00:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/08/the-well-of-saint-nobody-by-neil-jordan-review-the-film-makers-new-novel-is-full-of-marvels" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/games/2023/aug/08/paper-trail-the-unique-origami-video-game-henry-fred-hoffman" target="_blank">Paper Trail: the unique origami adventure that unfolds quite literally</a></h2><div class="description"> Henry and Fred Hoffman are the duo behind Norwich-based Newfangled Games. The game employs a spatial manipulation mechanic, allowing you to fold its planes and merge its sides to solve puzzles. You play as Paige, a budding academic leaving home for the first time to pursue her studies, spurred on by this unique ability.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:19:14 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/games/2023/aug/08/paper-trail-the-unique-origami-video-game-henry-fred-hoffman" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/ladies-first-a-story-of-women-in-hip-hop-review-a-joyous-painstaking-attempt-to-set-the-record-straight" target="_blank">Ladies First: A Story of Women in Hip-Hop review – a joyous, painstaking attempt to set the record straight</a></h2><div class="description"> 2023 marks the 50th anniversary of hip-hop. The origin point was a summer house party in the Bronx, during which DJ Kool Herc displayed a nascent style of turntabling. But glossing over the industry’s darker side is a missed opportunity.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 08:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/08/ladies-first-a-story-of-women-in-hip-hop-review-a-joyous-painstaking-attempt-to-set-the-record-straight" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Nightlife, loveseats and beautiful beaches: why the Caribbean makes for the perfect romantic holiday</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is an unbeatable destination for a romantic getaway. From Jamaica to the hidden gem that is Curaçao, there’s something to suit every couple, whether on honeymoon, celebrating an anniversary, or just escaping. Each of the many islands has its own unique history and vibe – and they all have plenty to offer.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:37:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Waterfalls, history and the world’s first underwater sculpture park: seven exciting things to do in the Caribbean</a></h2><div class="description"> The islands of the Caribbean are like nowhere else on Earth. From cocktails to coral reefs, they offer something for all tastes and tempos. Enjoy sunset cocktails on the white sand beaches of Barbados or Jamaica. Enjoy a classic mojito or piña colada at the heart of the reggae-infused warmth of Jamaica.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:36:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">From snorkelling to surfing: nine must-try Caribbean beach and water activities</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean offers a huge variety of tempting activities from snorkelling to scuba diving. Windsurfing and waterskiing is a must-try activity for everyone. Scuba diving is a great way to explore the most beautiful coral reefs imaginable. The Caribbean is home to some of the world’s most beautiful, vivid coral reefs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:38:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">From Pig Beach to Dunn’s River Falls: 10 must-visit Caribbean destinations – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is home to the world’s best beaches, pretty towns, waterfalls and national parks. Visit the Caribbean in all its glory. Visit the world's best beaches and waterfalls in the Caribbean. Visit CNN.com/Travel next Friday for more Caribbean travel stories.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:35:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/dollhouses-miniatures-popularity" target="_blank">Beyond the Barbie Dream House: why mini homes are having a big moment</a></h2><div class="description"> Growing interest in dollhouses suggests people find solace and joy in tiny things – especially when real homes are so pricey. The studio apartment came with modest furnishings: a small bed, a couch, books, a TV. The original dollhouse was a 1962 folding cardboard studio apartment.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:00:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/dollhouses-miniatures-popularity" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/08/snoring-slobs-and-splitting-the-bills-19-ways-to-holiday-with-friends-without-falling-out" target="_blank">Snoring, slobs and splitting the bills: 19 ways to holiday with friends – without falling out</a></h2><div class="description"> 65% of people planning to travel in the next 36 months will be doing so with friends. The sudden change from casual socialising to spending 24/7 together can be challenging. Here’s how to navigate some common sources of stress – and ensure you’re all still speaking to each other when you get home.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 04:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/08/snoring-slobs-and-splitting-the-bills-19-ways-to-holiday-with-friends-without-falling-out" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/my-partners-vagina-has-atrophied-and-she-is-struggling-to-reach-climax" target="_blank">My partner’s vagina has atrophied – and she is struggling to reach climax</a></h2><div class="description"> Following a hysterectomy, penetration is uncomfortable for her after 15 years of having sex. She has been unable to climax through penetration, which is new for her. Are there ways I can help? Send your story to iReport.com/help@dailymailonline.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:13:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/my-partners-vagina-has-atrophied-and-she-is-struggling-to-reach-climax" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/08/cycle-coast-to-coast-across-scotland-bike-kirkpatrick-c2c" target="_blank">Pedal the low road: cycling coast-to-coast across southern Scotland</a></h2><div class="description"> The Kirkpatrick C2C is a new 250-mile route across lowland Scotland and stops at bike-friendly hotels and cafes along the way. The route includes the MacDiarmid Memorial, a huge, metal sculpture of an open book, embellished with images from the work of the great poet.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 06:00:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/08/cycle-coast-to-coast-across-scotland-bike-kirkpatrick-c2c" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/british-gas-sends-382-demand-for-a-bill-i-dont-owe" target="_blank">British Gas sends £382 demand for a bill I don’t owe</a></h2><div class="description"> I’ve received a legal letter demanding a £382 ‘debt’ though I had switched to Bulb. I've been making regular monthly payments to the electricity company since January 2020. I was with British Gas for about a month before switching to Bulb.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 06:00:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/british-gas-sends-382-demand-for-a-bill-i-dont-owe" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/07/brotox-why-more-and-more-men-are-getting-tweakments" target="_blank">Brotox – why more and more men are getting tweakments</a></h2><div class="description"> The amount of money men spend on Botox has risen 400% since 2000. Brotox is a 34-year-old man with a history of Botox treatments. The most common Botox prescription is Botox, Botox and Botox injections in the UK.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 13:41:46 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/07/brotox-why-more-and-more-men-are-getting-tweakments" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/07/niger-thousands-gather-for-rally-to-cheer-coup-generals-as-junta-closes-airspace-video-report" target="_blank">Niger: thousands gather for rally to cheer coup generals as junta closes airspace – video report</a></h2><div class="description"> Thousands of coup supporters in Niger gathered on Sunday for a rally to cheer on the generals claiming power. The Ecowas bloc, chaired by the regional military powerhouse and Niger’s neighbour Nigeria, had given the troops that toppled President Mohamed Bazoum a week to return him to power.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 08:55:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/07/niger-thousands-gather-for-rally-to-cheer-coup-generals-as-junta-closes-airspace-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/01/bride-wades-through-floodwaters-after-philippines-hit-by-typhoons-video-report" target="_blank">Bride wades through floodwaters after Philippines hit by typhoons – video report</a></h2><div class="description"> The Philippines was hit with torrential rain over seven days, brought by Typhoon Doksuri and intensified by Typhoon Khanun. Low-lying villages to the north of the country were the worst affected. Residents were forced to travel by small wooden boats and roads were inundated.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 01 Aug 2023 12:10:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/01/bride-wades-through-floodwaters-after-philippines-hit-by-typhoons-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/31/wildfires-cross-us-border-into-canada-triggering-evacuation-order-video" target="_blank">Wildfires cross US border into Canada triggering evacuation order – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Firefighters are using water cannon from planes to try to control the blaze. Local authorities estimate the blaze is 885 hectares (2,200 acres) in size. Osoyoos has been ordered to evacuate after a wildfire crosses the border from Washington state of Washington.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 31 Jul 2023 08:44:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/31/wildfires-cross-us-border-into-canada-triggering-evacuation-order-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/video/2023/jul/26/sinead-oconnor-the-turbulent-career-of-the-irish-sensation-video-obituary" target="_blank">The life and career of Sinéad O’Connor: ‘I was really a protest singer’ - video obituary</a></h2><div class="description"> Sinéad O'Connor has died at the age of 56, prompting grief and tributes for a singer who enchanted and at times shocked the world. O’Connor’s family issued a brief statement on Wednesday evening announcing the death. The Dubliner enjoyed something of a renaissance in recent years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 26 Jul 2023 22:06:16 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/video/2023/jul/26/sinead-oconnor-the-turbulent-career-of-the-irish-sensation-video-obituary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/27/drone-footage-shows-aftermath-of-wildfires-on-2500-year-old-sicilian-temple-video" target="_blank">Drone footage shows aftermath of wildfires on 2,500-year-old Sicilian temple – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Wildfires have turned hills surrounding the temple of Segesta to ash after days of fires spreading across Sicily. The island has been devastated by wildfires that have killed at least three people, while heatwaves and severe storms affected the north of Italy. Local authorities said the blaze was put out around the archaeological site, but it is temporarily closed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:44:56 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/27/drone-footage-shows-aftermath-of-wildfires-on-2500-year-old-sicilian-temple-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten. He meets a friend from his past, Pepi Fernando, and they discuss what led to his radicalisation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Greece: wildfires rage on three islands and mainland – video report</a></h2><div class="description"> 64 of the 82 wildfires started on Sunday, the hottest day of the summer so far. The island of Rhodes forced 19,000 people to flee, and more than 1,000 have been evacuated. Wildfires also broke out on the island of Corfu and in the northern Peloponnese region.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 13:09:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/greece-wildfires-break-out-corfu-thousands-flee-rhodes-blazes-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Spain faces political gridlock after national elections – video report</a></h2><div class="description"> Pro-independence Catalan and Basque parties as potential kingmakers. People's party will be given first attempt at trying to cobble together enough votes to win a prime-ministerial investiture vote. If no candidate secures a majority within two months of the first vote on the prime minister, new elections must be held.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 12:11:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/24/spain-faces-political-gridlock-after-national-elections-video-report" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather. The Guardian's environment editor, Damian Carrington, explains what El Niño is and how it affects extreme weather.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian’s Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet a group that is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children's doorsteps. Playing Out aims to reclaim play space on the doorsteps of children's front door.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved the lives of millions and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office said global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high, and June is likely to follow suit. Experts said marine heatwaves have a similar impact on the environment as wildfires on land.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/uk-students-do-you-plan-to-live-at-home-during-university" target="_blank">UK students: do you plan to live at home during university?</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 90% of higher education students are worried about the rising cost of living. We want to speak to students who are living at home this year amid rising costs. Are you planning to commute in? Or are you going to live on campus? Are there other ways you plan on saving costs?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 12:33:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/2023/aug/08/uk-students-do-you-plan-to-live-at-home-during-university" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/03/tell-us-how-have-you-been-impcted-by-extreme-weather-in-britain" target="_blank">Tell us: how have you been impacted by extreme weather in the UK?</a></h2><div class="description"> We want to hear how people have been affected by heatwaves, storms and flooding in the UK in the last few years. Around the world, 2023 has been a year of deadly extreme weather, from wildfires in Greece to deadly heatwaves in India and Canada. We ask people to share their experiences of being affected by extreme weather.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 09:25:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/03/tell-us-how-have-you-been-impcted-by-extreme-weather-in-britain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/07/tell-us-about-the-lifestyle-changes-or-habits-you-have-adopted-to-stave-off-dementia" target="_blank">Tell us about the lifestyle changes or habits you have adopted to stave off dementia</a></h2><div class="description"> Jeremy Vine says he tries to prevent onset of dementia by listening to songs he hates. He was inspired to change his music habits after one of his friends said they were training their left hand to write in a bid to ward off dementia. Vine said he was inspired by a friend's friend who was training her to write with her left hand.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 11:53:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/07/tell-us-about-the-lifestyle-changes-or-habits-you-have-adopted-to-stave-off-dementia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/07/uk-school-leavers-have-you-been-turned-off-university-over-affordability-concerns" target="_blank">UK school leavers: have you been turned off university over affordability concerns?</a></h2><div class="description"> We're interested to hear from young Britons who have opted out of higher education because they feared student life would be unaffordable, or had concerns about their financial future if they attended university. We’d like to hear whether financial concerns relating to tuition fees, accommodation or graduate job prospects have prompted you to do an apprenticeship instead.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 09:57:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/07/uk-school-leavers-have-you-been-turned-off-university-over-affordability-concerns" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/08/summer-picks-should-we-ban-artificial-grass-podcast" target="_blank">Summer picks: should we ban artificial grass? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Madeleine Finlay speaks to Guardian feature writer Sam Wollaston and urban ecologist Prof Rob Francis about why people go for artificial grass, its environmental impact, and whether it’s time we rid ourselves of the idea of the perfect lawn altogether. Read about the plastic lawn backlash from this episode from April 2023.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 04:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/08/summer-picks-should-we-ban-artificial-grass-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">The legacy of Sinéad O’Connor – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Film-maker Kathryn Ferguson and journalist Simon Hattenstone share their memories of Sinéad O'Connor and reflect on her impact on music and society. Ferguson directed Nothing Compares, a 2022 documentary about the singer's life. She explains why O’Connor spoke out about abuse in the early 1990s when it was still taboo to do so.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/world-cup-england-nigeria-australia-denmark" target="_blank">Women’s Football Weekly: Lionesses find a way to win after James red card</a></h2><div class="description"> England beat Nigeria on penalties to reach the quarter-finals of the Women's World Cup. Lauren James will miss out after being sent off in the last 16 of the tournament. Andi Hickman, Faye Carruthers and Suzanne Wrack discuss the last three days of last-16 action.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 20:01:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/world-cup-england-nigeria-australia-denmark" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/efl-arsenal-shake-city-hoodoo-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">EFL back with a bang and Arsenal shake City hoodoo - Football Weekly podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Football Weekly is a weekly football podcast from the Guardian. This week's episode is hosted by Max Rushden, Ben Fisher, George Elek, Sanny Rudravajhala and Sanny Rudra. Listen to the latest episode of our weekly podcast, Football Weekly, on BBC One and Sky Sports.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 12:17:18 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/efl-arsenal-shake-city-hoodoo-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-hip-hop-gave-voice-to-a-generation-of-egyptians-hungry-for-change-podcast" target="_blank">How hip-hop gave voice to a generation of Egyptians hungry for change – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Music was vital to the early days of the Tahrir Square protests. The country is taking another authoritarian turn, that spirit of dissent cannot be extinguished, says The Guardian. Hip-hop gave voice to a generation of young Egyptians hungry for change, says the podcast podcast.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 04:00:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-hip-hop-gave-voice-to-a-generation-of-egyptians-hungry-for-change-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-can-we-escape-burnout-podcast" target="_blank">How can we escape burnout? | Podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Burnout is a serious issue in workplaces across the UK. What can we do to change our working culture in order to prevent it? Read the latest episode of our podcast How Can We Escape Burnout? Please email us at www.mailonline.co.uk.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 02:00:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/07/how-can-we-escape-burnout-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/07/people-are-under-siege-why-ethiopias-war-in-tigray-isnt-over" target="_blank">‘People are under siege’: why Ethiopia’s war in Tigray isn’t over</a></h2><div class="description"> Despite a peace deal last November, Eritrean troops remain in some border areas, and the Irob community is paying the price. Father Tesfaye* has shuttled secretly between his home district of Irob and Mekelle, the capital of Ethiopia’s northern Tigray region, ferrying sick people, medicines and small amounts of desperately needed food.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 10:16:53 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/aug/07/people-are-under-siege-why-ethiopias-war-in-tigray-isnt-over" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/san-quentin-prison-tour-interviews" target="_blank">As San Quentin prison vows to transform, its residents ask: is change possible?</a></h2><div class="description"> Governor Gavin Newsom wants to ‘completely reimagine what prison means’ by transforming the complex into a ‘modern’ prison. Lt Guim’Mara Berry was leading a media tour of California’s oldest prison, touting its acclaimed ‘262-to-life’ running club.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/san-quentin-prison-tour-interviews" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/ohio-special-election-issue-1-abortion-rights" target="_blank">What is the Ohio special election – and what does it mean for abortion rights?</a></h2><div class="description"> Ohio will hold a special election that could make it harder for the state’s voters to amend their own constitution. Republican lawmakers in May approved “Issue 1,” a proposal that would raise the threshold required to pass any future ballot measure from a simple majority to 60% of voters.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 10:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/08/ohio-special-election-issue-1-abortion-rights" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/07/brazilian-indigenous-reclaim-identities" target="_blank">‘I shout from the rooftops I exist’: Brazilians identifying as Indigenous up by 90% in 12 years</a></h2><div class="description"> A growing number of Brazilians are reclaiming their Indigenous identity, after years of fighting for rights. For a long time, being Indigenous was synonymous with being lazy, a good-for-nothing, a savage,’s Vahnessa de Oliveira Ferreira says.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 13:00:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/07/brazilian-indigenous-reclaim-identities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Sign up for the Fashion Statement newsletter: our free fashion email</a></h2><div class="description"> Style, with substance: what’s really trending this week, a roundup of the best fashion journalism and your wardrobe dilemmas solved, delivered straight to your inbox every Thursday. We’ve got something for you whether you love film, football, fashion or food.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 20 Sep 2022 11:06:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/jul/09/sign-up-for-word-of-mouth-the-best-of-guardian-food-every-week" target="_blank">Sign up for Word of Mouth: the best of Guardian Food every week</a></h2><div class="description"> A weekly email bringing you our best food writing, the latest recipes, seasonal eating ideas and must-read restaurant reviews. Sign up below to start receiving the best of our culinary journalism in one mouth-watering weekly email. We’ll send you latest recipes from Yotam Ottolenghi, Nigel Slater, Meera Sodha and all our star cooks.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 09 Jul 2019 08:19:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/jul/09/sign-up-for-word-of-mouth-the-best-of-guardian-food-every-week" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/gallery/2023/aug/08/portugal-wildfires-kittens-tuesday-best-photos" target="_blank">Portugal wildfires and tree-dwelling kittens: Tuesday’s best photos</a></h2><div class="description"> The Guardian's picture editors select photo highlights from around the world. Portugal's wildfires are the focus of this week's best photos. Portugal has been hit hard by wildfires in the past year and blamed for some of the country's worst fires in recent years. Click here for more from The Guardian.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 11:02:26 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/gallery/2023/aug/08/portugal-wildfires-kittens-tuesday-best-photos" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/08/the-women-calling-for-reform-of-venezuelas-severe-anti-abortion-laws-in-pictures" target="_blank">The women calling for reform of Venezuela’s severe anti-abortion laws – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> Despite demands for change, the government shows no sign of reforming the 1926 law. Only in 2000 was it amended to allow for abortions to save the life of the pregnant woman. Venezuelans have been turning to online sellers of abortion pills or paying for costly and illegal procedures in a doctor's office.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 07:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/08/the-women-calling-for-reform-of-venezuelas-severe-anti-abortion-laws-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/08/difference-is-beautiful-pregnant-trans-men-go-for-a-swim-in-pictures" target="_blank">‘Difference is beautiful’: pregnant trans men go for a swim – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The Seahorse Parents is a photography and film project in which four soon-to-be parents share their personal stories of what carrying future children as transgender men has been like. The project was set up by four men who are expecting to have children with gender-specific genital mutilation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 06:00:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/08/difference-is-beautiful-pregnant-trans-men-go-for-a-swim-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/08/2023-nature-infocus-photography-awards-winners-in-pictures" target="_blank">2023 Nature inFocus photography awards winners – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The results of the Nature inFocus photography awards were announced at a festival held at Jayamahal Palace in Bengaluru, India, on Monday 31 July. The awards honour photographers documenting unique natural history moments and critical conservation issues, and generate an impressive catalogue of imaginative and artistic images every year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 05:00:01 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/08/2023-nature-infocus-photography-awards-winners-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/07/a-ceasefire-in-tigray-but-in-the-displaced-peoples-camps-the-suffering-goes-on-in-pictures" target="_blank">A ceasefire in Tigray, but in the displaced peoples’ camps, the suffering goes on – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> About 1.8 million people were displaced because of fighting in the northern Ethiopian region. Despite an end to fighting, many people are still struggling to get enough food to survive. Ximena Borrazás and Edgar Gutierrez got rare access to the camps where many people still struggle for food.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 06:00:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/07/a-ceasefire-in-tigray-but-in-the-displaced-peoples-camps-the-suffering-goes-on-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr>
